<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5383.1.7>
    dc:creator "Brescovit, Antonio Domingos", "Ferreira-Sousa, Leonardo", "Motta, Paulo César", "Venticinque, Eduardo Martins" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "The more, the merrier: a new colonial species of the orb weaving spider genus Leucauge White, 1841 (Araneae: Tetragnathidae) from the Amazon rainforest" ;
    bibo:endPage "95" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-12-08" ;
    bibo:startPage "83" ;
    bibo:volume "5383" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301636>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301638>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301640>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301645>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301649> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301636>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Leucauge argyra (Walckenaer, 1841). A, Holotype and original label of Leucauge argyroaffins Soares & Camargo 1948 (MZSP 1330) (images by Nadine Dupérré). B, Female from Brasília, epigynum in lateral view (DZUB 3022). C–D pedipalp of male from Brasília (DZUB 4595). C, ventral view. D, retrolateral view. Leucauge behemoth n. sp., pedipalp of male paratype from Reserva Florestal Adolfo Ducke, Manaus (IBSP 97726). E, prolateral. F. ventral. G, retrolateral.Scale bars, A, 1.0 mm; B–G, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10301636/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301638>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Leucauge behemoth n. sp., female paratype from ARIE do Projeto Dinâmica Biológica de Fragmentos Florestais, Manaus (IBSP 97726). A,habitus, lateral. B, same, dorsal. C–F, Epigynum. C, ventral. D, posterior. E, dorsal, cleared. F, lateral. Scale bars, A, B, 1 mm; C–F, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10301638/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301640>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Living specimens of Leucauge behemoth n. sp. Female from Tambopata, Peru (photographed by Rich Hoyer/ Birdernaturalist in 20/IV/2019): A, female habitus, lateral. B, ventral. C, dorsolateral. D, specimens from Cantón Baños, Ecuador, coexisting without aggression outside their individual webs (photographed by Hederd Torres in 17/XII/2013)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10301640/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301645>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Leucauge behemoth n. sp. male and female from Manaus (IBSP 7382). A–B, epigynum. A, ventral. B, posterior. C–F, male palp. C, prolateral. D, retrolateral. E, retroventral. F, ventral. Scale bars, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10301645/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10301649>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Distribution of Leucauge behemoth n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10301649/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

